message: Always use the 'stove' on raw proteins and vegetables first. Avoid using 'water' entirely, as it seems to decrease value. Combine two cooked protein/vegetable items (e.g., cooked beef + cooked potato) to get 60 points. Then, add a third cooked protein or vegetable to this mix to reach 80 points. Cooked grains generally have 0 value and do not seem to increase the value of your combined dish, so avoid adding them to your high-value mixes. Once you reach 80 points, submit your inventory.
